OL,3,CFrom ministers to NHS doctors: Who is
OL,4,Cto blame for the infected blood
OL,5,Cscandal?
OL,7,FOn Monday, a seven-year public inquiry
OL,8,Fpublished its final report, which it
OL,9,Fsaid will provide a measure of justice
OL,10,Fto the thousands of people affected in
OL,11,Fwhat has been called the "biggest
OL,12,Ftreatment disaster in NHS history".
OL,14,FAccording to the report, the patients
OL,15,Fhad been failed "not once, but
OL,16,Frepeatedly" by doctors, the
OL,17,Fgovernment, the NHS, and others.
