OL,4,Cto blame for the infected blood
OL,5,Cscandal?
OL,7,FSir Brian Langstaff, inquiry chair,
OL,8,Fsaid Prof Bloom - who died in 1992 -
OL,9,F"must bear some of the responsibility
OL,10,Ffor the UK's slowness in responding to
OL,11,Fthe risks of Aids to people with
OL,12,Fhaemophilia".
OL,14,FAt the time, Prof Bloom said he was
OL,15,Funaware of any proven case in the UK
OL,16,Fand that there was no need to change
OL,17,Ftreatment.
