OL,3,CFrom ministers to NHS doctors: Who is
OL,4,Cto blame for the infected blood
OL,5,Cscandal?
OL,7,FAmong them is former prime minister
OL,8,FMargaret Thatcher, who reportedly said
OL,9,Fin a 1989 Downing Street meeting that
OL,10,Fpeople infected with HIV from blood
OL,11,Fproducts "had been given the best
OL,12,Ftreatment available on the then
OL,13,Fcurrent medical advice, and without it
OL,14,Fmany hemophiliacs would have died".
OL,16,FThe report called the statement a
OL,17,F"blanket line" that was
OL,18,F"inappropriate" and "unacceptable".
