OL,7,FShe also said the blood scandal
OL,8,Fvictims receiving compensation would
OL,9,Fbe "unfair" to other disabled people.
OL,10,FOther ministers echoed these words in
OL,11,Fsuccessive years.
OL,13,FAnother person mentioned in the report
OL,14,Fwas Kenneth Clarke, health minister at
OL,15,Fthe time, who was quoted writing in an
OL,16,F1983 Aids leaflet that there is "no
OL,17,Fconclusive proof" that Aids "may be
OL,18,Ftransmitted in blood or blood
OL,19,Fproducts".
