OL,7,FIt says: "On 25 February 1985, Kenneth
OL,8,FClarke, minister of state for health,
OL,9,Fstated, 'There has never been a
OL,10,Fgeneral state scheme to compensate
OL,11,Fthose who suffer the unavoidable
OL,12,Fadverse effects which can unhappily
OL,13,Farise from many medical procedures'...
OL,14,FIt set the tone for the government's
OL,15,Fresponse for many years."
OL,17,FThe report was also critical of the
OL,18,Fdelays to calling a public inquiry -
OL,19,Fblaming the then-prime minister
OL,20,FTheresa May for only announcing it in
OL,21,F2017 due to political pressure.
